  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The clinical use case has grown since the original validation campaign to include paediatric and low-body-weight adult patients, extending the operating flow range from 3–6 L/min down to 0.8–3 L/min. No re-calibration or supplemental validation evidence covering this expanded low-flow regime has been linked to this assessment.",
